HEADWORD: Handbill
<hw>Hand"bill`</hw> <pr>(-b⟦icr⟧l`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A loose, printed sheet, to be distributed by hand.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A pruning hook.</def> <altsp>[Usually written
<asp>hand bill</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Handbook</ent>⟦br⟧
